Bollywood pop star Daler Mehndi was found guilty by an Indian court on Friday of trafficking people into the United States during a tour in the late 1990s. Mehndi and his brother were accused of smuggling at least 10 people from India into the US in 1998 and 1999 by disguising them as part of singing troupe. The jobseekers subsequently stayed in the US and Canada illegally and attempted to find work. Read more: Slavery in India – 'an uncomfortable truth' Police initially filed charges in 2003 after a number of people came forward alleging the brothers took money from them but never took them abroad. Send  Facebook   Twitter   Google+   Whatsapp   
